grep: 
  Search for patterns within files.
  grep <pattern> <file>
awk: 
  A versatile text processing tool for pattern scanning and processing.
  awk '{print $1}' <file>
sed: 
  Stream editor for filtering and transforming text.
  sed 's/search/replace/g' <file>
cut: 
  Remove sections from each line of a file.
  cut -d' ' -f2 <file>
tr: 
  Translate or delete characters.
  echo "Hello" | tr '[:lower:]' '[:upper:]'
sort: 
  Sort lines of text files.
  sort <file>
uniq: 
  Report or omit repeated lines.
  uniq <file>
paste: 
  Merge lines of files.
  paste file1 file2
join: 
  Join lines of two files on a common field.
  join file1 file2
jq: 
  A lightweight and flexible command-line JSON processor.
  jq '.property' <json-file>
column: 
  Format input into a nicely aligned table.
  column -t <file>
